codex
I found one accounting issue before close-out: if the verifier uses its own ETH/WETH as seed capital, measuring only the ending WETH balance overstates profit by counting returned principal. I’m fixing that by normalizing both ETH and WETH into a single starting/ending WETH-equivalent wealth measure and wrapping any residual ETH at the end.
